  I. Adding the globus layer to your build
 II. Misc


I. Adding the globus layer to your build
=================================================

--- replace with specific instructions for the globus layer ---

In order to use this layer, you need to make the build system aware of
it.

Assuming the globus layer exists at the top-level of your
yocto build tree, you can add it to the build system by adding the
location of the globus layer to bblayers.conf, along with any
other layers needed. e.g.:

  BBLAYERS ?= " \
    /path/to/yocto/meta \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto-bsp \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-globus \
    "


